description: The user clicked on the "Start" button on the taskbar, which caused the Start Menu to open.
outcome: The Start Menu opened, replacing the mouse cursor which was previously hovering over the "Start" button.

description: The mouse click on "Control Panel" in the Start menu caused the tooltip describing the Control Panel to disappear.
outcome: The tooltip box describing the Control Panel disappeared.

description: The user clicked on the "Appearance and Themes" category in the Windows XP Control Panel. As a result, the category is highlighted.
outcome: The "Appearance and Themes" category is highlighted, likely indicating it is currently selected or being hovered over.

description: The user clicked the "Display" icon within the "Appearance and Themes" window.

event: The mouse clicked on DesktopScreen SverAppearanceSettings.
description: The user clicked on the "Screen Saver" tab within the "Display Properties" window.
outcome: The user interface has transitioned from the "Themes" tab to the "Screen Saver" tab. The preview pane now displays a screen saver preview, and the "OK" and "Apply" buttons have become active.

description: The user clicked the "None" option in the "Screen Saver" dropdown menu. As a result, the screen saver setting changed to "None."
outcome: The screen saver setting was changed to "None".

description: The user clicked the mouse on the "10" entry within the open "Wait:" dropdown menu.
outcome: The "Wait:" field changed to "10" and the open "Screen Saver" dropdown menu closed.

description: The user clicked the "Power" button within the "Screen Saver" tab of the "Display Properties" window. As a result, the "Power Options Properties" window opened.
outcome: A "Power Options Properties" window appeared, overlaying the "Display Properties" window and becoming the primary focus.

description: The user clicked the "Turn off monitor" dropdown menu, located within the "Settings for Home/Office Desk power scheme" section.
outcome: The "Turn off monitor" dropdown menu is expanded, suggesting it was likely clicked.

event: The mouse clicked on After 5 hours.
description: The user clicked the "After 5 hours" option within the "Turn off monitor" dropdown menu.
outcome: The "Turn off monitor" dropdown selection changed to "After 5 hours".

description: The user clicked the "Always On" option within the "Power schemes" dropdown menu.
outcome: The selected option in the "Power schemes" dropdown menu changed to "Always On".

event: The mouse clicked on Always On.
description: The user clicked the "Always On" option within the "Power schemes" dropdown menu.
outcome: The mouse cursor became visible and hovered over the "Cancel" button.

description: The user clicked the "Turn off hard disks" dropdown menu within the "Power Options Properties" window.
outcome: The "Turn off hard disks" dropdown menu expanded.

description: The user clicked the "After 20 mins" option within the "Turn off monitor" dropdown menu.
outcome: The "Turn off monitor" dropdown menu updated to display "After 20 mins".

description: The user clicked on "Never" in the "Turn off monitor" dropdown menu within the "Power Options Properties" window.
outcome: The "Turn off monitor" dropdown menu updated to display "Never" as the selected option, and the "Cancel" button became unhighlighted.

description: The user clicked the "OK" button in the "Power Options Properties" window.
outcome: The "Cancel" button became unhighlighted as the mouse cursor moved over the "OK" button.

description: The user clicked the "Cancel" button in the "Display Properties" window.
outcome: The "Cancel" button became unhighlighted, and the mouse cursor moved over the "OK" button.

description: The user clicked the "Display" icon, located below the "or pick a Control Panel icon" section.
